## Task 2 – Habit Tracker Functions (15 Marks)

We track habits with frequency and unit:

```haskell
data Unit = Daily | Weekly | Monthly
  deriving (Show)

convUnit :: Unit -> Float
convUnit Daily   = 1.0
convUnit Weekly  = 1/7
convUnit Monthly = 1/30

habits :: [(Float, Unit)]
habits = [(1.0, Daily), (2.0, Weekly), (3.0, Monthly)]
```

Goal: Write functions that convert `habits` into daily frequencies `r * convUnit u`.

1. recFreq – use simple recursion [2 marks]
2. tailFreq – use tail recursion [3 marks]
3. mapFreq – use map [1 mark]
4. foldrFreq – use foldr [2 marks]
5. foldlFreq – use foldl [2 marks]
6. comprFreq – use list comprehension [1 mark]

> All functions must have the same type. Provide the type signature for at least one. [2 marks]

